---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BookmarkIcon from '@assets/bookmark-icon-flat.svg';
import PenCircle from '@assets/pen-circle.svg';
import RcrPositiveChange from '@assets/portfolio/rcr-achieving-positive-change.png';
import ContentSection from '@components/ContentSection.astro';
import DesignProblemIcon from '@assets/design-problem-flat.svg';
---

<ContentSection>
  <BookmarkIcon
    slot="icon"
    style="color: var(--color-neutral-100); --icon-subject-color: var(--color-primary-800);"
  />

  <div slot="title" class="pb-8">Chapter Co-auther Contribution</div>
  <div slot="content">
    <p>
      <span class="font-bold">Recent progress in the sciences</span> behind adaptive
      learning technologies (for example, Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing,
      and Baysean Knowledge Tracing) are <span class="font-bold"
        >transforming the designer's ability to personalize</span
      > learning experiences based on individual learner's needs.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      For this reason a <span class="font-bold">new chapter was added</span> to the
      second edition of <span class="italic"
        >The Handbook on Learning and Instruction</span
      > discussing the <span class="font-bold text-primary-500"
        >current state of the science and how practicioners can apply it
        effectively</span
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      <span class="font-bold">As a co-author of this chapter</span>, I explored
      two questions from a designer's perspective:
    </p>
  </div>
  <div slot="read-more">
    <div
      class="flex items-center gap-8 mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm ring bg-card-bg ring-neutral-100 px-6 py-4"
    >
      <PenCircle
        class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0"
        style="color: var(--color-neutral-100); --icon-field-color: var(--color-primary-800);"
      />
      <div>
        Learners differ in a great many ways (knowledge state, interest, goals,
        affective state, strategic behaviors, learning styles, etc.), so <span
          class="font-bold text-primary-500"
          >which learner charactaristics should we adapt to?</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      class="flex items-center gap-8 mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm ring bg-card-bg ring-neutral-100 px-6 py-4"
    >
      <PenCircle
        class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0"
        style="color: var(--color-neutral-100); --icon-field-color: var(--color-primary-800);"
      />
      <div>
        Adaptions can happen in several time-frames (per action, per problem,
        per course, etc.), so <span class="font-bold text-primary-500"
          >which loops are effective at adapting to available data?</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ContentSection>
